column2: ENGLISH
China will grow larger.
You have been banished from the Kingdom of Pyongyang.
Beware the Americanist...
Consummatum Est! (It is finished!) -Dr. Jose P. Rizal at his execution
The good shine from afar, like the Himalaya mountains. But the wicked are unseen, like arrows shot in the night. -Dhammapada 304
People of Ezo combines traditions of Shinto and northern Japan's Ainu people.
By faith the flood is overcrossed. By vigilance the sea. By effort dukkha’s overcome. -Sutta Nipatta 1.10
Never shall the Malays vanish from the Earth, as long as they hold true to Islam.
However much a Dog barks at a Hill, it shall not collapse.
God may gives kings the divine rights to rule, but he can also take it away and give it to a common man who is more worthy of it if the king is unjust. -Letter to King of Gia Dinh
There are fish in the water and rice in the fields. -Sukhothai Inscription No. 1
Man found God and tried to make Him theirs. -Japanese proverb
They speak of the past and the future and keep repeating the same tender words as if they have an ocean of them. -Nguyen Du, The Tale of Kieu
The sky cannot have two suns, a nation cannot have two kings. -Cao Xuan Duc
To be rich is glorious -Hong Taizong
All diplomacy is continuing war by another means. -Zhou Enlai
Times are not always the same. The grass is not always green.  -Mongolian proverb
Even though the procession is long, it will still end up in church. -Philippine proverb
Happiness is not something ready made, it comes from your own actions. -HH XIV Dalai Lama
Within the span of hundred years of human existence, what a bitter struggle is waged between genius and destiny! -Lê Quân Thuy
To live desperately is to shine in life. -Oda Nobunaga
The responsibility for failure lies with the master, the achievement of success lies with the vassals. -Cao Cao
Pave the way for a grand peace for all the generations to come by enduring the unendurable and suffering what is insufferable. -Imperial Rescript

When one attains prosperity, another is sure to perish. It is the law of nature. -Anantathuriya
The Filipino is worth dying for. -Benigno Aquino Jr.
While the blanket is short, learn how to bend. -Philippine proverb
Love your country next to God, your honour, and most of all yourself. -Andres Bonifacio
Strength is defeated by strategy. -Philippine proverb
He who does not love his mother tongue is worse than a rotten fish. -Dr. Jose P. Rizal
